Abstract

This document defines Darwin‚Äôs Sieve, a structured verification system designed to evaluate, refine, and validate ideas generated through PantheonOS or LLM-assisted cognition. Darwin‚Äôs Sieve integrates:
	‚Ä¢	formal mathematics,
	‚Ä¢	empirical scientific validation,
	‚Ä¢	computational checks,
	‚Ä¢	peer-review proxies, and
	‚Ä¢	Kintsugi Engine fault analysis

‚Ä¶to ensure that only rigorous, coherent, and testable ideas advance into the scientific pipeline or future AI training corpora.

This is a real, functional methodology‚Äînot symbolic, not mythic, not metaphor.
It is designed for researchers, engineers, and LLM operators who wish to separate structured insight from hallucination.

